---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Terms of Use — Oakdene House Foundation"
  description="Terms of Use for the Oakdene House Foundation website at oakdenehouse.org.au."
>

  <!-- HERO -->
  <section class="legal-hero" aria-label="Terms of Use">
    <div class="container legal-hero__content">
      <nav class="breadcrumb" aria-label="Breadcrumb">
        <a href="/">Home</a>
        <span class="breadcrumb__sep" aria-hidden="true">/</span>
        <span aria-current="page">Terms of Use</span>
      </nav>
      <h1>Terms of Use</h1>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- DOCUMENT BODY -->
  <section class="section" aria-label="Terms of Use content">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="doc-wrap">

        <!-- Dates -->
        <div class="doc-meta">
          <p><em>Last updated: [Launch date to be inserted]</em></p>
          <p><em>Effective from: [Launch date to be inserted]</em></p>
        </div>

        <!-- Table of contents -->
        <nav class="doc-toc" aria-label="Page contents">
          <p class="doc-toc__heading">Contents</p>
          <ol class="doc-toc__list">
            <li><a href="#section-1">1. About us</a></li>
            <li><a href="#section-2">2. Purpose of the website</a></li>
            <li><a href="#section-3">3. Not professional advice</a></li>
            <li><a href="#section-4">4. Acceptable use</a></li>
            <li><a href="#section-5">5. Submitting information through forms</a></li>
            <li><a href="#section-6">6. Donations</a></li>
            <li><a href="#section-7">7. Third-party services and links</a></li>
            <li><a href="#section-8">8. Intellectual property</a></li>
            <li><a href="#section-9">9. AI chatbot and automated assistance</a></li>
            <li><a href="#section-10">10. Accuracy of information</a></li>
            <li><a href="#section-11">11. Availability</a></li>
            <li><a href="#section-12">12. Limitation of liability</a></li>
            <li><a href="#section-13">13. Children and young people</a></li>
            <li><a href="#section-14">14. Governing law</a></li>
            <li><a href="#section-15">15. Changes to these terms</a></li>
            <li><a href="#section-16">16. Contact</a></li>
          </ol>
        </nav>

        <!-- Intro -->
        <div class="doc-section">
          <p>These Terms of Use govern your use of the Oakdene House Foundation website at oakdenehouse.org.au ("the Website"). By accessing or using the Website, you agree to these terms. If you do not agree, please do not use the Website.</p>
        </div>

        <!-- Section 1 -->
        <div class="doc-section" id="section-1">
          <h2>1. About us</h2>
          <p>The Website is operated by Oakdene House Foundation (ABN 90 151 950 926), a registered Australian charity based at 29 Vine Street, Fairfield NSW 2165.</p>
        </div>

        <!-- Section 2 -->
        <div class="doc-section" id="section-2">
          <h2>2. Purpose of the website</h2>
          <p>This Website is intended to:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>Provide information about Oakdene's services, programs, and community initiatives</li>
            <li>Allow people to enquire about support, make referrals, apply to volunteer, and contact us</li>
            <li>Provide a directory of community support services</li>
            <li>Provide resources and information for community members, referrers, and partners</li>
            <li>Accept donations</li>
          </ul>
          <p><strong>The Website is not a crisis service, a medical service, or a substitute for professional advice. If you need immediate help, please see our <a href="/need-help-now/">Need Help Now page</a> or call 000 in an emergency.</strong></p>
        </div>

        <!-- Section 3 -->
        <div class="doc-section" id="section-3">
          <h2>3. Not professional advice</h2>
          <p>Information on the Website is general in nature. It is not intended as, and should not be relied upon as, medical, legal, financial, or professional advice. Always seek advice from a qualified professional for your specific situation.</p>
          <p>Oakdene's own services (counselling, programs) are provided under separate service agreements entered into when you engage with us directly.</p>
        </div>

        <!-- Section 4 -->
        <div class="doc-section" id="section-4">
          <h2>4. Acceptable use</h2>
          <p>When you use the Website, you agree not to:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>Use the site for any unlawful purpose</li>
            <li>Impersonate any person or misrepresent your identity or affiliation</li>
            <li>Submit false, misleading, or harmful information through our forms</li>
            <li>Attempt to gain unauthorised access to any part of the site, servers, or connected systems</li>
            <li>Interfere with or disrupt the Website or any user's access to it</li>
            <li>Upload or transmit any virus, malware, or other malicious code</li>
            <li>Use the Website to harass, abuse, or harm another person</li>
            <li>Collect or scrape personal information from the site</li>
            <li>Use any automated means (bots, scrapers, crawlers) except public search engines operating in good faith</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <!-- Section 5 -->
        <div class="doc-section" id="section-5">
          <h2>5. Submitting information through forms</h2>
          <p>When you submit information through forms on the Website (referral, volunteer, enquiry, or contact forms):</p>
          <ul>
            <li>You confirm that the information is true and accurate to the best of your knowledge</li>
            <li>Where you are referring another person, you confirm that you have the authority and consent to share their information</li>
            <li>You acknowledge that your submission will be handled in line with our <a href="/privacy-policy/">Privacy Policy</a></li>
            <li>You understand that Oakdene will respond within 2 business days where possible, but response times are not guaranteed</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <!-- Section 6 -->
        <div class="doc-section" id="section-6">
          <h2>6. Donations</h2>
          <p>Donations made through the Website are processed by Stripe Payments Australia and are final and non-refundable except where required by law or where a genuine error has occurred. If you have made a donation in error, please contact us at <a href="mailto:admin@oakdenehouse.org.au">admin@oakdenehouse.org.au</a> and we will work with you in good faith to resolve the issue.</p>
          <p>Tax-deductible receipts are issued for eligible donations where Oakdene holds Deductible Gift Recipient (DGR) status. If you do not receive a receipt within 7 business days, please contact us.</p>
          <p>Recurring donations continue until cancelled. You can cancel a recurring donation at any time by contacting us or using the cancellation link in your donation receipt email.</p>
        </div>

        <!-- Section 7 -->
        <div class="doc-section" id="section-7">
          <h2>7. Third-party services and links</h2>
          <p>The Website includes:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>Forms hosted on Jotform</li>
            <li>Payment processing through Stripe</li>
            <li>Links to external websites in the Service Directory and elsewhere</li>
          </ul>
          <p>These third-party services have their own terms and privacy policies. We are not responsible for the content, accuracy, or practices of external websites linked from our site. Links are provided as a convenience only and do not imply endorsement.</p>
        </div>

        <!-- Section 8 -->
        <div class="doc-section" id="section-8">
          <h2>8. Intellectual property</h2>
          <p>Unless otherwise indicated, all content on the Website — including text, images, logos, graphics, and design — is owned by or licensed to Oakdene House Foundation. You may:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>View, download, and print content for personal, non-commercial use</li>
            <li>Share links to pages on the Website</li>
            <li>Quote brief extracts with attribution to Oakdene House Foundation</li>
          </ul>
          <p>You may not:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>Reproduce, republish, or commercially exploit Website content without our written permission</li>
            <li>Remove or alter any copyright, trademark, or attribution notices</li>
            <li>Use our logo, name, or branding without permission</li>
          </ul>
          <p>Third-party content (such as stock photography or partner logos) is used with permission or under licence.</p>
        </div>

        <!-- Section 9 -->
        <div class="doc-section" id="section-9">
          <h2>9. AI chatbot and automated assistance</h2>
          <p>The Website may include an AI-powered chatbot to help answer common questions. You acknowledge that:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>Chatbot responses are generated by an AI model and may not always be accurate or complete</li>
            <li>The chatbot is not a counsellor, health professional, or crisis service</li>
            <li>For anything urgent, complex, or personal, you should contact our team directly or use the crisis lines on our <a href="/need-help-now/">Need Help Now page</a></li>
            <li>Conversations with the chatbot may be logged for quality improvement, in line with our <a href="/privacy-policy/">Privacy Policy</a></li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <!-- Section 10 -->
        <div class="doc-section" id="section-10">
          <h2>10. Accuracy of information</h2>
          <p>We make reasonable efforts to keep Website content accurate and up to date, but we do not guarantee that all information is current, complete, or error-free. Service details in the Service Directory in particular can change without notice — always confirm current eligibility, hours, and contact details with the listed service directly before acting on the information.</p>
        </div>

        <!-- Section 11 -->
        <div class="doc-section" id="section-11">
          <h2>11. Availability</h2>
          <p>We aim to keep the Website available at all times but do not guarantee uninterrupted access. The Website may be temporarily unavailable due to maintenance, technical issues, or circumstances outside our control.</p>
        </div>

        <!-- Section 12 -->
        <div class="doc-section" id="section-12">
          <h2>12. Limitation of liability</h2>
          <p>To the maximum extent permitted by law, Oakdene House Foundation, its directors, employees, and volunteers are not liable for any loss, damage, cost, or expense arising from your use of, or reliance on, the Website or its content — including indirect or consequential loss.</p>
          <p>Nothing in these Terms excludes any consumer guarantees or other rights that cannot legally be excluded under the Australian Consumer Law.</p>
        </div>

        <!-- Section 13 -->
        <div class="doc-section" id="section-13">
          <h2>13. Children and young people</h2>
          <p>The Website is not directed at children under 16. Where young people use our services, we handle their information with additional care and, where required, with parental or guardian consent.</p>
        </div>

        <!-- Section 14 -->
        <div class="doc-section" id="section-14">
          <h2>14. Governing law</h2>
          <p>These Terms are governed by the laws of New South Wales, Australia. Any dispute arising out of or in connection with these Terms will be subject to the exclusive jurisdiction of the courts of New South Wales.</p>
        </div>

        <!-- Section 15 -->
        <div class="doc-section" id="section-15">
          <h2>15. Changes to these terms</h2>
          <p>We may update these Terms from time to time. The most current version will always be available on our Website, with the "Last updated" date shown at the top. Continued use of the Website after changes constitutes acceptance of the updated Terms.</p>
        </div>

        <!-- Section 16 -->
        <div class="doc-section" id="section-16">
          <h2>16. Contact</h2>
          <p>For any questions about these Terms, please contact us at:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>Email: <a href="mailto:admin@oakdenehouse.org.au">admin@oakdenehouse.org.au</a></li>
            <li>Phone: <a href="tel:+61287170999">(02) 8717 0999</a></li>
            <li>Post: PO Box 988, Fairfield NSW 1860</li>
          </ul>
          <p><em>These Terms are written in plain language. They are a legal document but are not legal advice.</em></p>
        </div>

      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

</BaseLayout>

<style>
  /* ---- Hero ---- */
  .legal-hero {
    background-color: var(--color-primary);
    padding-block: 52px 44px;
  }

  .legal-hero h1 {
    color: var(--color-white);
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  /* ---- Document wrapper ---- */
  .doc-wrap {
    max-width: 760px;
    margin-inline: auto;
  }

  /* ---- Dates metadata ---- */
  .doc-meta {
    padding: 18px 22px;
    background-color: var(--color-tint);
    border-left: 3px solid var(--color-secondary);
    border-radius: 0 var(--radius-card) var(--radius-card) 0;
    margin-bottom: 36px;
  }

  .doc-meta p {
    margin-bottom: 4px;
    font-size: 0.9375rem;
    color: var(--color-muted);
  }

  .doc-meta p:last-child {
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  /* ---- Table of contents ---- */
  .doc-toc {
    background-color: var(--color-tint);
    border: 1px solid var(--color-secondary);
    border-radius: var(--radius-card);
    padding: 22px 28px;
    margin-bottom: 52px;
  }

  .doc-toc__heading {
    font-size: 0.8125rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: 0.07em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--color-primary);
    margin-bottom: 14px;
  }

  .doc-toc__list {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 7px;
    padding-left: 18px;
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  .doc-toc__list a {
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    color: var(--color-primary);
    text-decoration: none;
    transition: color var(--transition);
  }

  .doc-toc__list a:hover {
    color: var(--color-link-hover);
    text-decoration: underline;
    text-underline-offset: 2px;
  }

  /* ---- Document sections ---- */
  .doc-section {
    margin-bottom: 48px;
  }

  .doc-section:last-child {
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  .doc-section h2 {
    margin-bottom: 18px;
    padding-bottom: 12px;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-secondary);
    scroll-margin-top: 88px;
  }

  .doc-section p {
    font-size: 1rem;
    color: var(--color-text);
    line-height: 1.72;
    margin-bottom: 16px;
  }

  .doc-section p:last-child {
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  .doc-section ul,
  .doc-section ol {
    padding-left: 22px;
    margin-bottom: 16px;
  }

  .doc-section li {
    font-size: 1rem;
    color: var(--color-text);
    line-height: 1.65;
    margin-bottom: 7px;
  }

  .doc-section a {
    color: var(--color-primary);
    text-decoration: underline;
    text-underline-offset: 2px;
    transition: color var(--transition);
  }

  .doc-section a:hover {
    color: var(--color-link-hover);
  }
</style>
